      • read

        public Container read(InputStream inputStream)
               throws InvalidPackageException
        Parses an InputStream to produce a Container.
        Parameters:
        inputStream - An InputStream that contains a valid/parsable Container. This InputStream will be closed after reading.
        Returns:
        An instance of Container based on the data from InputStream. Does not verify the container/signature(s).
        Throws:
        InvalidPackageException - When the InputStream does not contain a parsable Container.
        ContainerReadingException - When there were issues parsing some elements of the Container. The parsed container and all encountered exceptions can be retrieved from this exception.

      • create

        public Container create(List<ContainerDocument> files,
                        List<ContainerAnnotation> annotations)
                 throws InvalidPackageException
        Creates a Container with the input documents and annotations and a signature covering them.
        Parameters:
        files - List of ContainerDocument to be added and signed. Can NOT be null.
        annotations - List of ContainerAnnotation to be added and signed. Can be null.
        Returns:
        A new Container which contains the documents and annotations and a signature covering them.
        Throws:
        InvalidPackageException - When the input data can not be processed or signing fails.
